metadata.author: Andy Stanton
metadata.description:
Shabba me whiskers! Its the fourth fantastic Mr Gum story, read by the author and with music and sound effects. A fantastic book for boys and girls aged 7-10 years old. 

Good evening, children, on this dark and windy night. Now, come gather round the fireplace, for tis time for strange tales to be spun.

Like the tale of Polly and that old tumbledown windmill by the riverside. But just what is the windmills terrible secret? Why is Mr Gum lurk-lurk-lurkin about? And how much does Old Granny know?

Gather closer, children, for all shall be revealed BRRR! SPOOKY!
